events.name: I/O Extended 2017 Limbe
events.description: Join us remotely take part in the Google's annual flagship conference, I/O 2017. With a lot of changes across Google's ecosystem; Android, Cloud, Firbase, Chrome, Tensor Flow and other open source libraries you are bound to find something interesting.

events.name: Njaka Africa Code Week 2017
events.description:
GDG Limbe is partnering with Njaka.org to organize Njaka Africa Code Week 2017.

We are inviting all kids aged 11-17 to join us for an intro to computer science. You do not need to come with a PC as we will provide them.

There are two tracks to choose from based on your interest:

- Develop a game with Scratch
- Build a website with JS/HTML/CSS

events.name: DevFest Fako 2017
events.description:
The DevFest Fako 2017 event is a three-days-long hack-streak aimed at getting students, developers and entrepreneurs from GDGs in Fako (GDG Buea and GDG Limbe ) to learn Google's technologies such as Firebase, Cloud And Tensorflow and use them to build a PWA utilising Firebase Cloud and Offline-first functions. We intend to develop this PWA during a two-day Firebase AppFest at Skylabase Inc.

More Info: https://www.meetup.com/preview/GDG-Buea/events/243045998

events.name: Limbe Local Guides Meetup
events.description: Techies and map lovers in and around Limbe will be meeting at the Zuoix office. Situated on the second floor of PressBook building in half Mile Limbe to discuss and update important aspects of the mapping situation in and around Fako.

events.name: Web Application Development Workshop
events.description: Free two-day hands-on workshop on HTML5, CSS3, Javascript, and PHP. We will also cover some Google services for web application developers like Google Cloud Platform, Google Maps and Forms. Trainers are Paul Mbua (CEO of Zixtech Organisation) Fongoh Tayong (Developer of DigitalRenter.com) and Zuo Bruno (CEO of Zuoix).

events.name: I/O Extended 2018 Limbe
events.description: I/O Extended 2018 Limbe brings developers from around Limbe to take part in the awesomeness of Google I/O via talks, hands-on learning with experts, and a first look at Google's latest developer products.

events.name: Walk Through on Firebase
events.description: This is an Intro to Google FireBase Event. Here we would walk through the basics of Firebase. This event will be live through the channel https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=chUImLIQqD0. Follow through and practice

events.name: DevFest + Firebase Limbe 2018
events.description: Bring along laptops for this event and for we would have live demos on Google's technologies such as Firebase, Cloud, and Tensorflow and use them to build befitting apps. During the event, we would have multiple talks on Cloud, Machine Learning with Tensorflow and also, we would have a code lab to build an app with Firebase technology.

events.description:
International Women Day
Theme: Empowered Women Empower Women

events.name: Docker workshop Tour: Limbe
events.description: Introducing Docker to the community and share Ideas on improving community activities

events.name: I/O Extended 2019 Limbe - Kotlin Intro
events.description:
In this event, we a recap on the Google I/O main event talks from entrepreneurs and motivational speakers. We would also get hands-on codelabs so attendees are strongly advised to bring their laptops.

We would offer breakfast, launch, and swags during the event.

We would also demo, apps build with Google technology for the Community.

Attendees would be provided a link to a feedback form at the end of the event to get their review.

Share this event with others and invite them to take part through this link.

Remember to include #io19extended in your tweets and posts to publicize the event.

events.name: Kotlin Everywhere Limbe 2019
events.description:
Kotlin is a general purpose, open source, statically typed “pragmatic” programming language for the JVM and Android that combines object-oriented and functional programming features. Kotlin is concise, type-safe and totally interoperable with Java and other JVM languages
Kotlin is Google's preferred language for Android development as well.

Are you interested in learning what Kotlin has to offer, are you interested in taking your Android development skills further and better with Kotlin, or you are just new and want to learn Kotlin? This is definitely a must-attend event for you.

Join GDG Limbe on the 6th of July in getting started with Kotlin, taking your Android development further as we will be presenting;
- Introduction to Kotlin
- Kotlin in Cloud
- Kotlin in Android applications development
There will be talk sessions and codelabs as well.

Target Audience:
Anyone interested in learning Kotlin.

What to Bring
- Laptops
- Notebooks
- Android studio setup (if you are interested in Android)
- Internet modems (optional)

There will be swags, snacks, and lunch for attendees.

events.name: DevFest Limbe 2019
events.description:
DevFest Limbe 2019 will be a one of a kind event in Limbe. Calling all developers around Limbe to meet and build a product on the 1st of November 2019 based on technologies they have been working on throughout this year, then showcase the products during a grand demo day on the 2nd of November 2019.

Diversity will be included in this event to share knowledge on various aspects of community building and promoting Women in Tech Community growth in Limbe.

We would also have refreshments and swags available in this event and each participant will get a participation badge.

1st November 2019 Friday Location: Zixtech HUB from 10am prompt (Hackerthon session)

2nd November 2019 Saturday : Location: Limbe 1 Council Hall (Savoy Palmz Road) from 9am Prompt (D&I session and main even)

A special D&I session for the Women Tech community will start the event on the 2nd of November from 9:00am

upcoming.name: Flutter Interact: Viewing Party, Limbe 2019
upcoming.description:
This year Flutter Team is hosting a major event, Flutter Interact, on Dec 11, 2019, to announce new features associated with Flutter and other related Google technologies.

GDG Limbe will run a viewing party with our Flutter enthusiast community members! Join the celebration!

We would also run a codelab session so please come along with your laptops.
